parameters.name: EndTimestamp
parameters.description: The time when the job stops running. Specify a UNIX timestamp representing the number of milliseconds that have elapsed since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 UTC.

parameters.name: GroupId
parameters.description: The application group ID. You can obtain the application group ID on the Application Management page in the SchedulerX console.

parameters.name: Line
parameters.description: The number of rows to return. The maximum number is 200.

parameters.name: Namespace
parameters.description: The namespace ID. You can obtain the namespace ID on the Namespace page in the SchedulerX console.

parameters.name: NamespaceSource
parameters.description: The source of the namespace. This parameter is required only for a special third party.

parameters.name: Offset
parameters.description: The number of offset rows. This parameter can be used for a paged query.

parameters.name: Reverse
parameters.description: Specifies whether to reverse the order. By default, the order is reversed.

parameters.name: StartTimestamp
parameters.description: The time when the job starts to run. Specify a UNIX timestamp representing the number of milliseconds that have elapsed since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 UTC.
